1. *Sudeći* po vremenskoj prognozi, sutra će biti sunčano. (Judging by the weather forecast, tomorrow will be sunny.)
2. *Sudeći* po njegovoj izjavi, on neće doći na sastanak. (Judging by his statement, he won't come to the meeting.)
3. *Sudeći* po mom mišljenju, ova odluka je najbolja za sve nas. (Judging by my opinion, this decision is the best for all of us.)
4. On je *sudio* na međunarodnom takmičenju u matematici prošle godine. (He judged at the international math competition last year.)
5. Sudija je *sudio* ovaj slučaj pošteno i pravedno. (The judge judged this case fairly and justly.)
6. Oni su *sudili* o njenom izgledu, a ne o njenim sposobnostima. (They judged her based on her appearance, not her abilities.)
7. Sud *sudi* u ovom slučaju već više od godinu dana. (The court has been judging this case for over a year now.)
8. Ona je *sudila* da je to najbolje rešenje za njihovu porodicu. (She judged that it was the best solution for their family.)
9. *Sudeći* po broju gostiju, ova kafana je veoma popularna. (Judging by the number of guests, this restaurant is very popular.)
10. Ona je *sudila* da neće biti dovoljno vremena da se sve uradi na vreme. (She judged that there wouldn't be enough time to do everything on time.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "sudeći" is a form of the verb "suditi" which means "to judge". The word can also function as a participle or a conjunction, depending on the context.